</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="172" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="11.[1422,2632,1845,2663]" pageId="11" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1423,1762,2395,2428]" pageId="11" pageNumber="172">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Endangered on The IUCNRed List.Jenkins’s Shrew 
<taxonomicName box="[1423,1518,2438,2467]" class="Mammalia" family="Tenrecidae" genus="Tenrec" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="11" pageNumber="172" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Tenrec</taxonomicName>
is known only from two specimens at the type locality, and its overall population is probably decreasing. It is believed to be geographically restricted and has an estimated extent of occurrence of only 1643 km?®. Specific habitat where it has been found is in decline, and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Major" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[1602,1683,2553,2586]" class="Mammalia" family="Tenrecidae" genus="Microgale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="11" pageNumber="172" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">major</taxonomicName>
threats are clearing offorest for agricultural land and fire.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
